dimension_type.ambient_light.help: How much ambient light there is. Should be a value between 0.0 and 1.0.
dimension_type.bed_works.help: If true, players can use beds to set their spawn and advance time. If false, beds will blow up when used.
dimension_type.coordinate_scale.help: Multiplier applied to coordinates when traveling between dimensions using a nether portal or /execute in.
dimension_type.fixed_time.help: Setting this value will keep the sun in a fixed position.
dimension_type.has_ceiling.help: Affects the weather, map items and respawning rules.
dimension_type.has_raids.help: If true, players with the Bad Omen effect can cause a raid.
dimension_type.has_skylight.help: Affects the weather, lighting engine and respawning rules.
dimension_type.height.help: The total height in which blocks can exist. Max Y = Min Y + Height.
dimension_type.infiniburn.help: Block tag defining what blocks keep fire infinitely burning.
dimension_type.logical_height.help: Portals can't spawn and chorus fruit can't teleport players above this height.
dimension_type.min_y.help: The minimum height in which blocks can exist.

dimension_type.natural.help: If true, portals will spawn zombified piglins. If false, compasses and clocks spin randomly.
dimension_type.piglin_safe.help: If false, piglins will shake and convert to zombified piglins.
dimension_type.respawn_anchor_works.help: If true, players can charge and use respawn anchors to set their spawn. If false, respawn anchors will blow up when used.
dimension_type.ultrawarm.help: If true, water will evaporate and sponges will dry.

generator_structure.spacing.help: The average distance in chunks between two structures of this type.

loot_pool.rolls.help: The amount of entries that are randomly chosen.
loot_pool_entry_type.alternatives.help: Tests conditions of the child entries and executes the first that can run.
loot_pool_entry_type.group.help: Executes all child entries when own conditions pass.
loot_pool_entry_type.loot_table.help: Adds the contents of another loot table.

noise_settings.bedrock_floor_position.he: Position of the bedrock floor. Higher numbers move the floor up.
noise_settings.bedrock_roof_position.hel: Relative position of the bedrock roof starting at the world height. Higher numbers move the roof down.
noise_settings.disable_mob_generation.he: If true, mobs will not spawn during generation.
noise_settings.name: Name
noise_settings.noise.bottom_slide.help: Adds or removes terrain at the bottom of the world. Does nothing when size is 0.
noise_settings.noise.bottom_slide.offset: Defines an range of 'Offset * Size Vertical * 4' blocks at the bottom of the world where the density is set to the target.
noise_settings.noise.bottom_slide.size.h: Defines a range of 'Size * Size Vertical * 4' blocks where the existing density and target are interpolated.
noise_settings.noise.bottom_slide.target: The target density. Positive values add terrain and negative values remove terrain.
noise_settings.noise.density_factor.help: Determines how much the height influences the terrain. Positive values produce land at the bottom. Values close to 0 produce uniform cave-like terrain.
noise_settings.noise.density_offset.help: Affects the average terrain height. A value of 0 produces terrain land height at half the height. Positive values raise the height.
noise_settings.noise.height.help: The total height where blocks can generate. Max Y = Min Y + Height.
noise_settings.noise.island_noise_overri: If true, terrain will be shaped like islands similar to the end.
noise_settings.noise.min_y.help: The minimum height where blocks start generating.
noise_settings.noise.top_slide.help: Adds or removes terrain at the top of the world. Does nothing when size is 0.
noise_settings.noise.top_slide.offset.he: Defines an range of 'Offset * Size Vertical * 4' blocks at the top of the world where the density is set to the target.
noise_settings.noise.top_slide.size.help: Defines a range of 'Size * Size Vertical * 4' blocks where the existing density and target are interpolated.
noise_settings.noise.top_slide.target.he: The target density. Positive values add terrain and negative values remove terrain.
